org.pircbotx.hooks.managers

Class GenericListenerManager<E extends PircBotX>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pircbotx.hooks.managers.GenericListenerManager<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ListenerManager<E>
    Deprecated. 
    Due to multiple new functions of PircBotX theat depend on multiple threads, this class is deprecated and is only kept for legacy reasons or special cases. Use of this class will have unexpected results. All bots should now use ThreadedListenerManager.

    @Deprecated
public class GenericListenerManager<E extends PircBotX>
extends Object
implements ListenerManager<E>
    Generic ListenerManager based off of a normal event system. This is backed by a simple HashSet

    Please note: This is a very basic manager offering little security and features. Any long running listener will block all bot operations since its executed in the same thread. Adding any listeners during bot operation ( Eg PircBotX's waitFor method) in another thread is risky since the set might be in use already, throwing a ConcurrentModificationException.

    Author:
    Leon Blakey
    See Also:
    ThreadedListenerManager
